pyplot defaults

Sometimes you don't want to define figure sizes and such for each different figure. This function helps set some reasonable defaults so you don't have to.

{% raw %}

set_plt_defaults[source]

set_plt_defaults(figsize=(10, 10), spines_off=['top', 'right'])

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

What does a plot look like before setting defaults?

{% raw %} 
import numpy as np
rnd = np.random.random(10)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
plt.plot(rnd)

[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7f9728a9ed50>]
{% endraw %}

What about after?

{% raw %} 
set_plt_defaults()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
plt.plot(np.random.random(10))

[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7f9728baa610>]
{% endraw %}

Removing ticks and spines

remove_ticks[source]

remove_ticks(ax, xticks_off=True, yticks_off=True, spines=['top', 'bottom', 'left', 'right'])

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
fix, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(rnd)
remove_ticks(ax, spines=['top','right'])
